Oh, for cryin' out loud.

5
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:14,145
Listen, fella, l already gave.

6
00:02:18,087 --> 00:02:20,920
Do you understand English?

7
00:02:42,412 --> 00:02:45,848
Long flight, huh?
Bombay to DC?

8
00:02:54,824 --> 00:03:00,285
You know, l always wondered.
Do they serve, like, lndian food on the plane?

9
00:03:01,531 --> 00:03:04,864
lf there's anything else
l can do for you, sir...

10
00:04:55,144 --> 00:04:59,911
- The things that land in your in-box, huh?
- Good morning. l'm sorry l'm late.

11
00:04:59,983 --> 00:05:02,816
l didn't see the case file yet.
The traffic's terrible.

12
00:05:02,919 --> 00:05:07,253
Takes longer to get crosstown
than it does a plane ride from lndia.

13
00:05:07,323 --> 00:05:10,486
Which is where our victim
flew in from last night - Bombay.

14
00:05:10,593 --> 00:05:13,585
- Who are we talking about?
- Hugh Potocki.

15
00:05:13,663 --> 00:05:16,564
lmporter/exporter from Minneapolis.
Laid over in DC.

16
00:05:16,632 --> 00:05:18,998
All this blood drains from his body.

17
00:05:19,102 --> 00:05:21,900
- Did the ME see it? The body?
- Yeah.

18
00:05:21,971 --> 00:05:26,635
Tox test ruled out hemorrhagic fever,
Ebola, anything exotic.

19
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:30,110
Something killed this man,
but it wasn't any foreign disease.

20
00:05:30,179 --> 00:05:31,942
- No sign of forced entry?
- No.

21
00:05:32,015 --> 00:05:34,609
No one was seen
comin' or goin' from this room.

22
00:05:34,684 --> 00:05:40,452
The maid found the body 20 minutes after
a bellman left Mr Potocki. lt happened fast.

23
00:05:40,523 --> 00:05:43,515
So what you're saying is
that nobody knows anything.

24
00:05:43,626 --> 00:05:47,153
But then l guess
that's why it's in your in-box.

25
00:05:51,167 --> 00:05:55,126
So what do you think, Agent Scully?
Haunted hotel room?

26
00:05:55,204 --> 00:05:58,173
Alien invaders? Sloppy vampires?

27
00:06:00,476 --> 00:06:05,106
There is one small thing.
The cops missed it their first time around.

28
00:06:09,485 --> 00:06:14,684
- A child's print.
- Yeah. That's what it looks like.

29
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:20,629
There was a ring of thieves
when l was back in New York.

30
00:06:20,696 --> 00:06:23,494
They used kids for B and E jobs.

31
00:06:23,566 --> 00:06:26,660
Squeezin' in through cracked windows,
that kind of thing.

32
00:06:26,736 --> 00:06:29,000
But this, this is beyond.

33
00:06:29,072 --> 00:06:32,371
No. From what l see, Agent Doggett,

34
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:35,069
from the way this man died,

35
00:06:35,178 --> 00:06:37,510
l doubt it was a kid who did this.

36
00:06:37,580 --> 00:06:40,515
Thanks. l'm not ready
to lose all my faith in humanity.

37
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:43,416
But regardless,

38
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:46,920
l'd say it's wise you keep an open mind.

39
00:06:51,461 --> 00:06:57,093
The better the economy gets,
the harder it is to fill these kinds ofjobs.

40
00:06:58,267 --> 00:07:02,863
And the problem is that people look at it
as just a pay check.

41
00:07:02,939 --> 00:07:06,170
They don't realize that,
as Maintenance Engineer,

42
00:07:06,242 --> 00:07:09,405
you are playing an important part
in these kids' lives.

43
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,776
And l can't tell you how wonderful it is

44
00:07:11,881 --> 00:07:16,284
to find someone as enthusiastic
as you are, Mr Burrard.

45
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:22,180
And l understand you can start immediately?

46
00:07:27,797 --> 00:07:29,458
That's wonderful.

47
00:07:35,138 --> 00:07:40,474
- Big fella, isn't he?
- Big is a relative term, Agent Doggett.

48
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,569
lt took three strong men
to wheel him in here.

49
00:07:44,647 --> 00:07:47,582
He tipped the scale at 402 pounds.

50
00:07:47,650 --> 00:07:50,778
Hugh Potocki was a big man
with big appetites.

51
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:53,913
Loved big cars, big houses,
big business.

52
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:59,292
Divorced twice. He carried two alimonies,
one with child support.

53
00:07:59,395 --> 00:08:04,492
Never missed a payment. ln fact,
he seems to have spoiled his wives and kids.

54
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:09,162
- l'm missing the point.
- lt seems he loved big women too.

55
00:08:09,272 --> 00:08:11,604
Considering the evidence and motives,

56
00:08:11,674 --> 00:08:14,939
we can probably rule out
his ex-wives as suspects.

57
00:08:15,011 --> 00:08:19,141
Well, considering what l found here today,
l'd say l have to agree.

58
00:08:23,853 --> 00:08:29,086
Tissue damage. Massive trauma
to the lower intestine and the rectal wall.

59
00:08:29,158 --> 00:08:32,150
ls that from something
goin' in or comin' out?

60
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:36,288
Unfortunately, there's so much damage
that it's hard to tell.

61
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:42,033
l took MRls, which reveal further shredding
throughout the abdomen

62
00:08:42,138 --> 00:08:44,766
and into the stomach area.

63
00:08:47,343 --> 00:08:51,780
lndia's a major transit point
for the golden triangle.

64
00:08:51,847 --> 00:08:55,613
