courier of heroin or opiates? A drug dealer?

66
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:05,791
Fills a latex balloon with heroin, swallows it.
We've all seen this kind of thing before.

67
00:09:05,861 --> 00:09:08,659
But what if somebody got to him en route,

68
00:09:08,731 --> 00:09:13,794
forcibly extracted the drugs,
tearin' it from his stomach?

69
00:09:13,869 --> 00:09:18,499
l'd say that's a good theory, Agent Doggett.
Not to mention a graphic one.

70
00:09:18,574 --> 00:09:22,977
But there would have been traces left
of drugs in his system.

71
00:09:23,045 --> 00:09:26,811
Nor does it account for the blood loss
that this man experienced.

72
00:09:26,882 --> 00:09:30,750
Then we're right back where we started.
Nobody knows anything.

73
00:09:30,853 --> 00:09:32,878
Not exactly.

74
00:09:33,556 --> 00:09:38,220
l ran a decay analysis
to determine the time of death.

75
00:09:38,894 --> 00:09:43,490
Liver temperature, buildup of gases,
extent of rigor - routine stuff.

76
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:47,662
lt's not 100 per cent accurate,
but it gives us a range.

77
00:09:47,737 --> 00:09:51,833
- What's the range?
- 24 to 36 hours.

78
00:09:54,410 --> 00:09:56,776
Well, that's just wrong.

79
00:09:56,879 --> 00:10:01,213
lt would mean that Mr Potocki here
would have died before he left Bombay.

80
00:10:01,284 --> 00:10:05,618
No. lt would mean that a dead man
boarded a plane in lndia,

81
00:10:05,721 --> 00:10:08,918
changed planes in Paris,
hailed a cab at Dulles

82
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:12,586
