Agent Scully.

84
00:10:16,432 --> 00:10:18,525
l told you to keep an open mind.

85
00:10:34,483 --> 00:10:36,815
- Look what you did to my scooter.
- lt's mine.

86
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:39,911
- Yeah, right.
- You gonna take it from me?

87
00:10:40,489 --> 00:10:42,457
Hey.

88
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:45,618
Leave him alone.

89
00:10:45,728 --> 00:10:48,253
What's goin' on here, Quinton?

90
00:10:49,498 --> 00:10:53,127
l know you. Your name's Trevor?

91
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:58,263
You're in seventh grade, right? Got nothing
better to do than pick on sixth graders?

92
00:10:58,341 --> 00:11:00,172
- He ran into me.
- Liar.

93
00:11:00,276 --> 00:11:02,141
Enough.

94
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:05,236
You wanna be a bully?
Find somebody your own age.

95
00:11:06,482 --> 00:11:09,747
l'll talk to your father if l have to.

96
00:11:10,486 --> 00:11:12,579
Come on, Quinton.

97
00:11:46,021 --> 00:11:48,546
Yes. Thank you.

98
00:11:48,657 --> 00:11:50,989
Sorry to wake you.

99
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:53,119
Goodbye.

100
00:11:53,195 --> 00:11:55,629
- Bad connection?
- Consulate in New Delhi.

101
00:11:55,698 --> 00:12:01,728
Three weeks ago an American businessman
was found dead in his hotel room. Look.

102
00:12:01,837 --> 00:12:06,536
A Mr Albert Brecht of Spokane.
The reports were hard to piece together.

103
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:10,203
The medical records are in Hindi.
The death certificate's in Farsi.

104
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:15,716
And the news accounts are in...
l don't know, letters l've never seen before.

105
00:12:16,719 --> 00:12:21,713
But l did get you a translation
of Mr Brecht's autopsy results.

106
00:12:24,427 --> 00:12:27,726
lnternal trauma.
Tearing in the abdomen.

107
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:31,732
You're the doctor. lt sounds like
the same MO, doesn't it, Agent Scully?

108
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:34,701
Look at this.
Brecht's passport was a recent issue.

109
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:37,830
lt has his weight at 205 pounds.

110
00:12:37,907 --> 00:12:40,171
Whereas here, an lndian medical examiner

111
00:12:40,242 --> 00:12:44,736
has him listed at 238 pounds
just two hours after his death.

112
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:49,682
Well, if there's one thing people lie about,
it's their weight.

113
00:12:49,752 --> 00:12:55,122
That's a pretty big lie.
l mean, that's a 33-pound discrepancy.

114
00:12:55,224 --> 00:12:58,250
Well, he was a big man, that's for sure.

115
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:01,261
Yeah.

116
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:04,059
As was our DC victim.

117
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:08,602
All the better for accommodation.

118
00:13:11,774 --> 00:13:14,038
Accommodation?

119
00:13:16,979 --> 00:13:22,611
Well, something has to account
for the weight gain, Agent Doggett.

120
00:13:25,454 --> 00:13:34,795
What if whatever it is that killed these men
entered and exited them of its own free will?

121
00:13:37,266 --> 00:13:42,329
l mean, something small, with small hands,

122
00:13:43,939 --> 00:13:52,244
living inside the victims
as a stowaway of sorts.

123
00:13:54,116 --> 00:13:58,678
You know l agree that having an open mind
is important to crime solving, but

124
00:13:58,787 --> 00:14:05,522
this theory of yours requires an openness
that l'm just not comfortable with.

125
00:14:05,628 --> 00:14:09,120
l understand, Agent Doggett.

126
00:14:09,198 --> 00:14:11,792
And l can't prove it,

127
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:17,828
but l bet that if we had weighed Hugh Potocki
when he first arrived here from Bombay,

128
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:21,000
that he would have been
33 pounds heavier than his corpse.

129
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:26,605
lt's a theory, Agent Scully, but to my mind -
and pretty much the rest of me -

130
00:14:26,682 --> 00:14:29,116
it doesn't work.

131
00:14:29,184 --> 00:14:32,119
l appreciate your resistance.

132
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:35,890
But so far this evidence supports it.

133
00:14:36,559 --> 00:14:39,289
Except one thing.

134
00:14:40,029 --> 00:14:46,298
Even if there was something living inside of
Hugh Potocki when he arrived from Bombay,

135
00:14:46,368 --> 00:14:49,394
you said that Mr Potocki was already dead.

136
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:23,161
Dad.

137
00:15:23,238 --> 00:15:25,433
Dad? Dad. Dad. Dad.

138
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,673
- Quint, what is it?
- There's a man in here.

139
00:15:28,744 --> 00:15:31,269
What?

140
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:35,942
- What are you talking about?
- He was here, Dad. Right over there.

141
00:15:36,051 --> 00:15:38,747
- He had no legs.
- Quinton.

142
00:15:41,757 --> 00:15:43,725
Quinton, listen to me.

143
00:15:43,792 --> 00:15:49,059
Things that you imagine,
things that you dream, they're not real.

144
00:15:50,065 --> 00:15:54,729
- And what's not real can't hurt you.
- But, Dad, it was real. lt was.

145
00:15:54,803 --> 00:15:57,772
Quint, there's nobody here.

146
00:16:02,945 --> 00:16:05,937
Try to get some sleep. OK?

147
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:46,281
Dad?

148
00:16:57,866 --> 00:16:59,959
Dad?

149
00:17:51,420 --> 00:17:54,480
The first dead body l saw,
l was 19 and a marine.

150
00:17:55,724 --> 00:17:58,557
This boy... Criminy.

151
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:00,651
Yeah.

152
00:18:01,864 --> 00:18:05,823
- That's not all he claims he saw.
- That's what the cops told me.

153
00:18:05,901 --> 00:18:09,166
That's why l thought
we should come down here.

154
00:18:09,238 --> 00:18:13,937
He said he called his dad in
because there was something in his room.

155
00:18:14,743 --> 00:18:19,339
l asked him to describe it.
He said that it was a munchkin.

156
00:18:21,283 --> 00:18:23,877
That it had no legs.

157
00:18:23,952 --> 00:18:27,786
And that it was keeping itself up
with its arms.

158
00:18:30,292 --> 00:18:33,921
That's a pretty good trick,
