Which got me thinking that if these siddhi
hold so fast to their orthodoxy,

230
00:28:15,276 --> 00:28:20,111
then what would cause them
to break their faith?

231
00:28:20,548 --> 00:28:23,449
- l don't know.
- Something human.

232
00:28:25,453 --> 00:28:27,512
Revenge?

233
00:28:27,622 --> 00:28:29,783
Maybe.

234
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:38,024
This is an American chemical plant
in a village in lndia called Vishi.

235
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:42,035
lt's just outside of Mumbai,
which is better known to us as Bombay.

236
00:28:42,137 --> 00:28:45,402
About six months ago
the plant inadvertently released

237
00:28:45,507 --> 00:28:49,375
a small cloud of methyl isocyanate gas.

238
00:28:50,678 --> 00:28:55,206
118 of Vishi's mostly indigenous
population were killed.

239
00:28:55,884 --> 00:28:58,375
But it wasn't very well reported over here.

240
00:28:58,486 --> 00:29:03,014
l spent all night cross-checking
the victims of the disaster.

241
00:29:03,091 --> 00:29:07,221
And one finally caught my attention.

242
00:29:08,029 --> 00:29:10,520
Now, it's... Oh, here.

243
00:29:10,598 --> 00:29:12,896
lt's an 11-year-old boy

244
00:29:13,001 --> 00:29:17,938
whose father is described as being
a holy man of the Chamar caste.

245
00:29:18,039 --> 00:29:20,405
The beggar caste.

246
00:29:20,508 --> 00:29:24,911
Fakirs and mystics are,
well, often of low birth.

247
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:29,848
Do you think that this boy's father could be
a siddhi mystic like you described?

248
00:29:29,918 --> 00:29:35,618
He could be. But if he's out for revenge, then
why is he killing the people that he's killing?

249
00:30:15,463 --> 00:30:18,125
What's the matter with you?

250
00:30:18,233 --> 00:30:19,666
Nothing.

251
00:30:19,767 --> 00:30:24,227
Trevor. Where are you going?
Dinner's on the table.

252
00:30:27,408 --> 00:30:29,638
Trevor?

253
00:30:30,812 --> 00:30:32,905
Trevor, dinner.

254
00:30:35,149 --> 00:30:37,140
Trevor.

255
00:30:42,357 --> 00:30:43,585
Trevor.

256
00:31:13,621 --> 00:31:15,680
Excuse me.

257
00:31:28,570 --> 00:31:31,835
She came out to call her son in for dinner.

258
00:31:33,207 --> 00:31:35,505
That's all we know.

259
00:31:35,577 --> 00:31:38,239
What are we doin' here? Cos l'm not sure.

260
00:31:38,346 --> 00:31:41,338
What are we doing?

261
00:31:41,416 --> 00:31:47,218
A woman died of mysterious circumstances
not three blocks away from a previous victim.

262
00:31:47,322 --> 00:31:50,485
External signs are a direct match.

263
00:31:51,893 --> 00:31:55,192
- That woman's eyes.
- l saw her eyes.

264
00:31:55,263 --> 00:31:59,563
But dollars to doughnuts, there wasn't
anything that crawled up inside her.

265
00:31:59,667 --> 00:32:01,828
l think we're reachin' here.

266
00:32:01,903 --> 00:32:05,361
Maybe you're seein' things
that you wanna see.

267
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:10,207
- Are you questioning my integrity?
- No, l'm questionin' the whole damn case.

268
00:32:10,278 --> 00:32:14,009
From your so-called expert,
to the evidence you've chosen to ignore,

269
00:32:14,082 --> 00:32:17,848
to the fact that your approach has got us
no closer to a pattern or a motive

270
00:32:17,919 --> 00:32:21,116
or even catchin' this killer
than we were when we started.

271
00:32:21,222 --> 00:32:23,452
l asked you to keep an open mind.

272
00:32:23,558 --> 00:32:28,791
Yeah, well, l try to keep an open mind,
but it tends to shut my eyes.

273
00:32:28,896 --> 00:32:31,592
There is something here, Agent Doggett.

274
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:35,262
And l'll admit that it's hard to accept.

275
00:32:36,137 --> 00:32:41,268
But there is a motive and there is a pattern
and there is a reason.

276
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:45,306
And we will see it.

277
00:32:45,413 --> 00:32:47,472
But not working like this.

278
00:32:48,116 --> 00:32:50,209
Yeah, well.

279
00:32:51,219 --> 00:32:53,619
l hope somebody sees it.

280
00:33:04,565 --> 00:33:06,556
Trevor?

281
00:33:07,935 --> 00:33:11,462
- Trevor, l'm Dana Scully...
- What happened?

282
00:33:11,572 --> 00:33:15,099
- Your father's in the house. l'm gonna take...
- Where's my mom?

283
00:33:15,176 --> 00:33:17,804
Trevor.

284
00:33:17,912 --> 00:33:20,506
He was here.

285
00:33:20,615 --> 00:33:22,674
The little man.

286
00:33:22,784 --> 00:33:26,515
l saw him. He followed me.

287
00:33:47,675 --> 00:33:50,803
Agent Doggett? Where is he?

288
00:33:50,878 --> 00:33:52,869
ls that him?

289
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:56,643
lf you mean the janitor,
yeah, that's him, right in there.

290
00:33:56,718 --> 00:33:59,687
Agent Scully called and said that

291
00:34:00,855 --> 00:34:04,689
you had arrested what might be an
honest-to-goodness siddhi mystic.

292
00:34:04,792 --> 00:34:06,953
Agent Scully jumped the gun on that one.

293
00:34:07,028 --> 00:34:12,193
The only thing extraordinary about this man
is he doesn't speak, to anyone.

294
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:14,291
Where is Agent Scully?

295
00:34:14,368 --> 00:34:18,236
She left, after four hours
of attempting to interrogate this guy.

296
00:34:18,339 --> 00:34:22,173
Unless he jumps up and does something
mystical in the next ten minutes,

297
00:34:22,243 --> 00:34:24,507
we're releasin' him.

298
00:34:27,215 --> 00:34:29,843
- What are you doin'?
- The man sitting there

299
00:34:29,917 --> 00:34:32,909
may not be the man sitting there.

300
00:34:34,889 --> 00:34:37,255
No one may be there at all, in fact.

301
00:34:38,059 --> 00:34:41,688
Not in the next ten minutes, there ain't.

302
00:34:44,065 --> 00:34:46,158
Oh, wow.

303
00:34:47,368 --> 00:34:49,529
Agent Doggett?

304
00:34:50,938 --> 00:34:53,907
You gotta take a look at this.

305
00:35:13,194 --> 00:35:16,527
Come on. lt's a trick.

306
00:35:16,597 --> 00:35:19,430
Yeah, but not of the camera.

307
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:31,372
Wait, if he's not there...

308
00:35:31,445 --> 00:35:34,107
He could be anywhere.

309
00:35:41,455 --> 00:35:44,390
- Yes?
- Sir, l am so sorry to bother you again.

310
00:35:44,458 --> 00:35:48,918
- l know this has been a terrible ordeal.
- Yes. What is it you need?

311
00:35:48,996 --> 00:35:52,397
l need to speak
with your son Trevor again.

312
00:35:52,466 --> 00:35:54,627
ls this about his mother?

313
00:35:54,735 --> 00:35:57,727
Well, Trevor told me that he saw a man.

314
00:35:57,805 --> 00:36:02,833
There's just something that doesn't quite
add up, and l need to be certain.

315
00:36:04,345 --> 00:36:07,007
Thank you.

316
00:36:07,114 --> 00:36:08,741
Scully.

317
00:36:08,816 --> 00:36:12,752
l think you ought to get back here,
Agent Scully. There's somethin'...

318
00:36:12,820 --> 00:36:17,519
- What?
- The janitor, he's here but he's not.

319
00:36:17,625 --> 00:36:19,752
l can't explain it.

320
00:36:19,827 --> 00:36:23,024
- Trevor's not in his room.
- Just hang on one second.

321
00:36:23,130 --> 00:36:27,362
Agent Doggett,
what do you mean, he's not there?

322
00:36:31,539 --> 00:36:34,099
- Who's that?
- Hello?

323
00:36:39,847 --> 00:36:42,008
Mr Burrard.

324
00:36:42,116 --> 00:36:46,644
l thought you... Well, l didn't expect
to see you back at work.

325
00:36:55,162 --> 00:36:58,825
This is the agent who picked him up before.

326
00:36:58,900 --> 00:37:01,926
Can you make this call?

327
00:37:11,145 --> 00:37:13,841
Here he comes.

328
00:37:47,415 --> 00:37:50,407
Trevor? Are you there?

329
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:39,832
- Get out of there.
- The windows are locked.

330
00:38:39,934 --> 00:38:41,993
Break 'em, OK?

331
00:39:07,128 --> 00:39:09,153
l'll get help.

332
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:22,370
- Oh, thank God.
- Do something.

333
00:39:24,178 --> 00:39:26,874
Quinton, what's the matter?

334
00:39:30,384 --> 00:39:33,979
lt's him. lt's the little man.

335
00:39:34,055 --> 00:39:37,047
Who? Trevor?

336
00:39:37,158 --> 00:39:41,117
All right, now, you boys,
you just stop playing around.

337
00:39:41,195 --> 00:39:43,288
OK, don't move.

338
00:39:45,132 --> 00:39:48,363
- Stay where you are.
- Wait, what are you doing?

339
00:39:48,469 --> 00:39:50,699
Stop him. Shoot him.

340
00:39:55,209 --> 00:39:56,699
l can't.

341
00:40:10,157 --> 00:40:13,422
- Oh, my God.
- What is it? What happened?

342
00:40:13,527 --> 00:40:15,586
Agent Scully?

343
00:40:17,164 --> 00:40:19,155
Scully?

344
00:41:13,954 --> 00:41:16,650
You gonna be OK, Agent Scully?

345
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:21,661
l got a drift of what happened
in there to you.

346
00:41:22,563 --> 00:41:24,622
l mean, sorta.

347
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:35,836
l shot a young boy.

348
00:41:39,013 --> 00:41:42,073
The good news is, you're wrong.

349
00:41:44,451 --> 00:41:47,147
But it's what l saw.

350
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:51,452
With my eyes, anyway.

351
00:41:53,327 --> 00:41:57,286
Do you know what it's like
not to be able to trust your own eyes?

352
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:02,435
Then why'd you shoot him?

353
00:42:14,181 --> 00:42:17,116
Because it's what the boy saw.

354
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:23,154
And in an instant,

355
00:42:24,191 --> 00:42:29,151
l realized that it's what Mulder
would have seen, or understood.

356
00:42:30,164 --> 00:42:33,497
Because that's just how he came at things -

357
00:42:33,567 --> 00:42:36,661
withoutjudgment and without prejudice,

358
00:42:36,737 --> 00:42:40,969
and with an open mind
that l am just not capable of.

359
00:42:49,183 --> 00:42:52,414
lt's been a long night.

360
00:42:52,519 --> 00:42:55,420
Give yourself a break.

361
00:42:56,924 --> 00:43:00,189
This whole thing didn't make any sense.

362
00:43:02,029 --> 00:43:04,088
No.

363
00:43:05,232 --> 00:43:07,325
lt did.

364
00:43:10,271 --> 00:43:13,001
ln some way, it did.

365
00:43:26,053 --> 00:43:27,680
No, thanks.

366
